Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the architecture and techniques of a wireless communication system, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper talks about transmission mode selection and interference suppression, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the distributed storing capabilities in edge devices, which can be related to hardware architecture. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper talks about cooperative radio resource management, which involves distributed computing. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the system architecture and key techniques of F-RANs, which can be related to systems and control.
